p: In the District Court for the Third Judicial District of the Territory of Washington holding terms at Seattle in and for the Counties of King, Kitsap & Snohomish
In re Ah Sing and Ah Yoel } Habeas Corpus

And now Octo: 25 1873 this case was heard and signed at Chambers upon Petition, Writ and Return, and the Court order that the above named prisoners be discharged from Custody and that the Respondent Frederick Minick pay the costs of this proceeding within 20 days from this date for a Machment to issue
